markets.title: Will a hurricane category 5 hurricane or stronger hit coastal Texas this year?
markets.subtitle: Category 5 or higher
markets.rules_primary: If the National Weather Service reports that a maximum sustained wind-speed of at least 157 miles per hour (corresponding to a hurricane category  or stronger) in coastal Texas (see below for more details) that occurred between August 11, 2023 and November 30, 2023, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary:
The Exchange uses two NWS products for its Underlying: (1) the Daily Climate Reports for Corpus Christi, Victoria, McAllen, Laredo, Harlingen, Brownsville, Houston-Intercontinental, Houston-Hobby, Galveston, College Station, and Palacious, Texas; and (2) any location within a city listed above included in an NWS Post-Storm Hurricane Report.

The market will expire on the first 10:00 AM ET following the release of official data at the Underlying confirming the event has occurred. Otherwise, the market will expire on the sooner of the the first 10:00 AM ET following the release of data for November 30, 2023, or one week after November 30, 2023.
